messages.message: Hey codyy, I have a PR that looks to have had a successful run (https://jenkins.instabase.com/job/instabase/view/change-requests/job/PR-69652/) yesterday but this success didn't translate to the github PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/69652). Trying to re-run the failed test doesn't resolve this issue, and tips here on getting the PR checks to pass?

Hm, what was your method to rerun the test?
I'm mostly curious if the steps I shared yesterday were flawed :joy:

Oh, I was rebuilding from github UI, and then checked the job page to see if there was a successful run. I just clicked `Build Now` from jenkins and see the github pre-merge checks is now in progress again. soo false alarm, these instructions look correct :pray:

Oh good! Yea it was a weird scenario, sorry the normal rebuild process doesn't work for these one-off incidents. Fortunately it's a one-off situation overall and won't recur, so after this one updates the status it should be good going forward!
